<section xml:id="section-assignment-week7">
  <title>Week 7 Assignment</title>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Invert these matrices. (Show the steps of your process, though
        you don't need to show every row operation in the row
        recursion.) (6)
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            \begin{pmatrix}
              2 \amp -2 \amp 2 \\
              1 \amp -1 \amp -1 \\
              3 \amp 1 \amp 1
            \end{pmatrix}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \begin{pmatrix}
              0 \amp 4 \amp -3 \\
              3 \amp -1 \amp 0 \\
              1 \amp -2 \amp -1
            \end{pmatrix}
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider the transformation defined by this matrix. (6)
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            0 \amp 2 \amp 0 \\
            1 \amp 1 \amp 0 \\
            0 \amp -1 \amp 1
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          What does this matrix do to the line
          <me>
            \Span \left\{ \begin{pmatrix}
              1 \\ 1 \\ 3\
            \end{pmatrix} \right\} 
          </me>.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          What does this matrix do to the plane given by the equation     
          <me>
            x - y - z = 0 
          </me>.
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this matrix and its associated transformation. (8) 
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            1 \amp 1 \amp -1 \\
            0 \amp 1 \amp 3 \\
            2 \amp 4 \amp -1
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the kernel and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the image and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Check that the dimension of the image and the kernel add up
          to the dimension of the domain.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find the rank of the matrix. 
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this matrix and its associated transformation. (8) 
        <me>
          \begin{pmatrix}
            1 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\
            0 \amp 0 \amp 1 \amp 1 \amp 1
          \end{pmatrix}
        </me>
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the kernel and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find a basis for the image and state its dimension.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Check that the dimension of the image and the kernel add up
          to the dimension of the domain.
        </p></li>
        <li><p>
          Find the rank of the matrix. 
        </p></li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>m \gt n</m> and we have a matrix representing a
        transformation <m>\RR^n \rightarrow \RR^m</m>, what are the
        maximum and minimum dimensions of the column and rowspaces of
        the matrix? What are the maximum and minimum dimensions of
        the kernel and image of the transformation? (Give reasons for
        your maxima and minima.) (6) 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>
